video.title: Pokémon Journeys: The Series
video.synopsis: Young trainer Ash and his new friend Goh become research fellows at Professor Cerise's laboratory, traveling all over the world to learn about Pokémon.

episodes.synopsis: Though he's excited to attend Professor Oak's Pokémon camp, Ash oversleeps when the day arrives. Newcomer Goh is just as excited — and on time.
episodes.title: Enter Pikachu!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Oak invites Ash to the opening ceremony for Professor Cerise's new lab in Vermilion City. Goh sets out to catch a legendary Pokémon.
episodes.title: Legend? Go! Friends? Go!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Cerise asks Ash and Goh to investigate the sudden appearance of Ivysaur in Vermilion City, but the two researchers disagree on their methods.
episodes.title: Ivysaur's Mysterious Tower

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh head to the Galar region on assignment. During their stopover, some Pokémon steal Ash's backpack — with Ash and Goh's train tickets inside!
episodes.title: Settling the Scorebunny!

episodes.synopsis: Once they get off the train, Ash and Goh set out on the hunt for Dynamax Pokémon. Meanwhile, a Scorbunny is hot on their trail.
episodes.title: Mind-Boggling Dynamax

episodes.synopsis: After learning more about the Pokédex functions on their Rotom Phones from Professor Cerise, Ash and Goh head out to catch some local Pokémon.
episodes.title: Working My Way Back to Mew!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh travel to the Hoenn region, where Ash has entered Goh into the Battle Frontier Flute Cup. Their first opponents are Hodge and his Hariyama.
episodes.title: Serving Up the Flute Cup!

episodes.synopsis: After the team finds an exhausted Piplup, they set out for Snowpoint City in the Sinnoh region to reunite it with its trainer. Team Rocket follows.
episodes.title: The Sinnoh Iceberg Race!

episodes.synopsis: The internet is full of reports that legendary Pokémon Ho-Oh has been seen in the Johto region. The researchers head to Ecruteak City to check it out.
episodes.title: Finding a Legend!

episodes.synopsis: After a ship's captain reports being saved by a Dragonite, Goh and Ash set out in search of the Dragonite island that they believe exists ... somewhere.
episodes.title: A Test in Paradise!

episodes.synopsis: While the laboratory staff deal with a mysterious power outage, Chloe contemplates her future and her relationship with Pokémon.
episodes.title: Best Friend ... Worst Nightmare!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Cerise gives Ash and Goh tickets to the World Coronation Series finals in the Galar region, where the strongest trainers battle for glory!
episodes.title: Flash of the Titans!

episodes.synopsis: When a Gigantamax Drednaw interrupts the World Coronation finals in pursuit of Team Rocket, Ash, Goh and their Pokémon spring into action!
episodes.title: The Climb to Be the Very Best!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh travel to the Unova region, where they head to the newly discovered Ruins of the Titan site at Desert Resort to search for Pokémon.
episodes.title: Raid Battle in the Ruins!

episodes.synopsis: After snow in Vermilion City forces Professor Cerise to shut down the lab for system maintenance, Goh heads home for a few days to visit his family.
episodes.title: A Snow Day for Searching!

episodes.synopsis: Gengar's hauntings at the lab resume. Ash and Goh vow to capture the poltergeist Pokémon, and Professor Cerise explains the lab's paranormal history.
episodes.title: A Chilling Curse!

episodes.synopsis: After Darmanitan taunts Scorbunny in a practice battle, Scorbunny is determined to learn the Ember attack, but getting Goh's attention is a challenge.
episodes.title: Kicking It from Here into Tomorrow!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh head to the Vermilion Gym, where Ash challenges the substitute Gym Leader as his first World Coronation Series opponent.
episodes.title: Destination: Coronation!

episodes.synopsis: Goh and Ash visit a film set, where the star, a Ditto, flees after a fight with the director. They search for her, but she's fallen in with Team Rocket!
episodes.title: A Talent for Imitation!

episodes.synopsis: Pokémon Orienteering day dawns bright and early, with Ash, Goh and Professor Cerise each leading a group of kids on a trek through Vermilion City.
episodes.title: Dreams Are Made of These!

episodes.synopsis: After learning about Pokémon Eggs, Goh wants to find one. Ash's latest World Coronation Series match ends with him feeling like someone is calling him.
episodes.title: Caring for a Mystery!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh head to the Hoenn region to witness the annual migration of Beautifly, but first they have to find them. Goh's Raboot starts acting out.
episodes.title: Goodbye, Friend!

episodes.synopsis: Someone seems to be stealing the food that the researchers leave out for Pokémon in Cerise Park. To catch the culprit, Ash and Goh camp out.
episodes.title: Panic in the Park!

episodes.synopsis: Team Rocket are sent to the Sinnoh region for a vacation, but their break is interrupted by the arrival of Ash and Goh looking for a special Pokémon.
episodes.title: A Little Rocket R & R!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh head to the Kalos region, where Goh wants to catch Kalos Pokémon and Ash sets his sights on a World Coronation Series Battle Festival.
episodes.title: A Festival Reunion!

episodes.synopsis: Goh enters his giant Magikarp in the tenth annual Magikarp High Jump Tournament. Then he and Ash head to Slowpoke Island, hoping to catch a Slowpoke.
episodes.title: Splash, Dash, and Smash for the Crown!

episodes.synopsis: Professor Cerise gives Ash and Goh tickets to a World Coronation Series Master Class battle in Galar, with challenger Raihan battling champion Leon.
episodes.title: Toughing It Out!

episodes.synopsis: A Sobble sneaks up on Ash and Goh while they're eating at the Wyndon Pokémon Center. To catch it, they have to follow a trail of crying people.
episodes.title: Sobbing Sobble!

episodes.synopsis: Yamper brings home an injured Pidove, so Professor Cerise and his family decide to nurse it back to health. Chloe has her hands full keeping the peace!
episodes.title: There's a New Kid in Town!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Riolu are on a roll after the latest World Coronation Series battle, and Pikachu is jealous! When Ash's mom visits, Pikachu follows her home.
episodes.title: Betrayed, Bothered, and Beleaguered!

episodes.synopsis: Chloe asks Ash and Goh to step in at her younger brother Parker's school: His friend Nami is upset that other kids say her Feebas isn't cute.
episodes.title: The Cuteness Quotient!

episodes.synopsis: Goh joins his parents for a family vacation in the Johto region. Walking through the woods, he recalls meeting another trainer there three years ago.
episodes.title: Time After Time!

episodes.synopsis: The local Pokémon Center is hosting a Pokémon trading event. When Ash and Goh head over to check it out, they meet a trainer who's a Bug-type enthusiast.
episodes.title: Trade, Borrow, and Steal!

episodes.synopsis: Ash travels to Saffron City to battle his next opponent, but when he learns that the Karate Master has been defeated, he challenges the victor instead.
episodes.title: Solitary and Menacing!

episodes.synopsis: Goh decides to catch a Pikachu, and Professor Cerise informs him about a mass outbreak of Pikachu in the mountains. But Team Rocket is on the hunt too!
episodes.title: Gotta Catch a What?!

episodes.synopsis: After Ash battles new opponents in the World Coronation Series, the Cerise Laboratory researchers head to the Hoenn region to investigate a sandstorm.
episodes.title: Making Battles in the Sand!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh head to the Alola region and reunite with Professor Kukui, Professor Burnet and Ash's human and Pokémon friends at the Pokémon School.
episodes.title: That New Old Gang of Mine!

episodes.synopsis: With Chloe in tow, Ash and Goh visit the Pewter Museum of Science. Goh heads to a public dig site to find a Fossil Pokémon, but Team Rocket is there!
episodes.title: Restore and Renew!

episodes.synopsis: Goh and Ash travel to the Cianwood Gym in the Johto region so Ash can take on Bea in a World Coronation Series rematch.
episodes.title: Octo-Gridlock at the Gym!

episodes.synopsis: When a hot day in Vermilion City turns thunderous, Ash, Goh and Professor Cerise suspect that the Legendary bird Pokémon Zapdos is somewhere nearby.
episodes.title: A Crackling Raid Battle!

episodes.synopsis: While Meowth battles a cold, Jessie and James review a video of Ash's Pikachu. On a forest walk, Ash and Goh try to help a wild Marshtomp.
episodes.title: Pikachu Translation Check!

episodes.synopsis: Ash and Goh set out for the Galar region to investigate the Dynamax phenomenon. During a train delay, they meet strange Pokémon in a mysterious forest.
episodes.title: Sword and Shield, Slumbering Weald!

episodes.synopsis: While Goh and Sonia investigate the Darkest Day in Turffield, Team Rocket infiltrates the Galar Energy Plant, with Ash and Leon heading there too.
episodes.title: Sword and Shield: The Darkest Day!

episodes.synopsis: Ash heads to Stow-on-Side to meet Sonia and Goh, who conclude that the Darkest Day is a Pokémon. At the Energy Plant, Leon encounters it directly.
episodes.title: Sword and Shield: From Here to Eternatus!

episodes.synopsis: At the stadium, Leon and Team Rocket are no match for Eternatus. Ash takes on Chairman Rose while Goh battles Oleana to break through and end the chaos.
episodes.title: Sword and Shield... The Legends Awaken!

episodes.synopsis: When Psychic energy is detected on Cero Island, Ash and Goh head out in hopes of finding Mew. When they get there, they meet an old foe: Mewtwo!
episodes.title: Getting More Than You Battled For!

episodes.synopsis: The Vermilion City Pokémon Eating Contest is on, and Ash, Goh and their Pokémon are competing for a trip to Unova. Team Rocket wants to win too.
episodes.title: Crowning the Chow Crusher!

episodes.synopsis: Setting out on Goh's prize trip, Ash and Goh arrive in Castelia City. Unbeknownst to them, Team Rocket is lying in wait to kidnap Pikachu!
episodes.title: A Close Call... Practically!
